<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 15 at 3:46PM MDT  by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southeastern
Madison, eastern Beaverhead and south central Gallatin Counties
through 445 PM MDT...
At 345 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 15
miles west of Henrys Lake, moving east at 35 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
West Yellowstone, Targhee Pass, Raynolds Pass, Lakeview, Yellowstone
Village and Red Rock Pass.
This includes the following highways...
Highway 191 between mile markers 1 and 10, and between mile markers
31 and 32.
Highway 287 between mile markers 1  and 13.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
